list.abstract: moral（英[ˈmɒrəl]，美[ˈmɔːrəl]），英语单词，作形容词用，为道德的；能尊奉道德规范的；有道德观念的。作名词用，为道德教训；寓意；道德。短语搭配有moral issue（道德问题；道义问题；德育问题），例句为“The moral here is don't retire.（这里的寓意是不要退休。）” moral形容词类近义词有psychological、ethical，名词类近义词有overtone，反义词有immoral。morally是moral的副词形式。
Moral（モラル），编剧。 2022年2月3日，担任编剧的电视剧《汗皂交香》定档在日本播出。

yingyinNormal.en: Because power in the hands of those who lack honesty, lacks a moral compass. And without a moral compass, power runs amok.
yingyinNormal.zh: 权力如果掌握在不诚实的人手里，便会失去道德的指引。而失去了道德的指引，权力便会胡作非为。

yingyinNormal.en: I have with me Fordyce's Sermons which speak very eloquently on all matters moral.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我随身带着《讲道集》，这是本关于行为道德的善辩集。

yingyinNormal.en: There's a good moral in this data: your brain, and by extension you, might care more about the very negative, immoral things another person has done compared to the very positive, moral things, but it's a direct result of the comparative rarity of those bad behaviors.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有个不错的道德故事和这资料有关：你的大脑，延伸出去就是你会比较在乎另一个人所做的非常负面、非常不道德的事情，而非十分正面且道德的事，但这个直接的结果存在于相对及少数的坏行为之中。

yingyinNormal.en: On one hand, learning very negative, highly immoral information about someone typically has a stronger impact than learning very positive, highly moral information.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一方面，知道关于某人非常负面、非常不道德的信息，基本上会有更强的影响，相对于得知某人有非常正面、道德的信息。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, you're the good guy. You're our moral compass.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是个好人，你是我们的道德楷模。

yingyinNormal.en: No right legally, no. But we think he has a moral right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他在法律上没权利，但道义上还是有的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, if you're looking for the moral of the story, you could simply ask.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你是要找故事的寓意，你大可以直接开口问。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, complicated moral situation? No right, No wrong? You have to tell David.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道的，复杂的道德情况，是没有错或对。你必须要告诉大卫。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, the Lions technically won, but it was a moral victory for the Green Bay, Mermen.
yingyinNormal.zh: 技术上来说狮队赢了，但在士气方面是绿湾美人鱼队赢了。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't, because the universe depends on it. Nice. Good, moral compass. We're straight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我必须如此，因为这事关宇宙的命运。好。好三观。我们没问题了。

yingyinNormal.en: And the key to life is to develop an internal moral emotional GPS that can tell you which way to go.
yingyinNormal.zh: 命运的关键在于培育出一个内在的道德情感导航仪，使其能够为你指明方向。

yingyinNormal.en: Plus, you've got that pesky moral conscience. God, that stuff gets in the way. He thinks he's the good guy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另外你还有讨厌的良心，这玩意儿最碍事了，他老把自己当好人。

yingyinNormal.en: Are there any moral constraints on this person? We have international law. On this earth, every act is a political act.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对这个人有任何道德约束吗？我们有国际法，在地球上，超人的行为都是政治行为。

yingyinNormal.en: However, if crew moral is better served by my roaming the halls weeping, I would gladly defer to your medical expertise. Excuse me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然而，如果大家能在我的指挥下忠诚地为星舰服务的话，我会很高兴接受你的专业医疗意见的。
